      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tunneling:</strong> under-packed tip or wet paper → dry the tip, tamp gently, toast edge before lighting.</li>
        <li><strong>Canoeing:</strong> over-packed one side → roll between fingers to redistribute; wet the fast side lightly.</li>
        <li><strong>Harsh draws:</strong> grind too fine or stuffed → loosen top 1 cm, re-tamp lightly.</li>
        <li><strong>Goes out:</strong> too loose → tamp mid-body with packing tool; relight after a small pull.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
